Product Listing changes:

- add options to enable/disable columns to the admin configuration section
- individual column can be enabled/disabled by setting the following keys to a value:

  PRODUCT_LIST_IMAGE
  PRODUCT_LIST_MODEL
  PRODUCT_LIST_NAME
  PRODUCT_LIST_MANUFACTURER
  PRODUCT_LIST_QUANTITY
  PRODUCT_LIST_PRICE
  PRODUCT_LIST_WEIGHT
  PRODUCT_LIST_BUY_NOW

- to disable a column, sets its value to 0
- to enable a column, sets its value to a non-zero integer;
- the values will also be used to determine the columns' order

  e.g. if you wish to display Model, Name, Price and Buy Now columns in that order, 
       you should set:
  
       Keys                        Value
       -------------------------   -----
       PRODUCT_LIST_IMAGE            0
       PRODUCT_LIST_MODEL            1
       PRODUCT_LIST_NAME             2
       PRODUCT_LIST_MANUFACTURER     0
       PRODUCT_LIST_QUANTITY         0
       PRODUCT_LIST_PRICE            3
       PRODUCT_LIST_WEIGHT           0
       PRODUCT_LIST_BUY_NOW          4

  e.g. if you wish to display Image, Name, Manufacturer Name, Price and Buy Now columns
       in that order, you should set:
  
       Keys                        Value
       -------------------------   -----
       PRODUCT_LIST_IMAGE            1
       PRODUCT_LIST_MODEL            0
       PRODUCT_LIST_NAME             2
       PRODUCT_LIST_MANUFACTURER     3
       PRODUCT_LIST_QUANTITY         0
       PRODUCT_LIST_PRICE            4
       PRODUCT_LIST_WEIGHT           0
       PRODUCT_LIST_BUY_NOW          5

******************
**** IMPORTANT ***
******************

If you have defined any of these keys in local/configure.php, please remove them before
running the new product listing code.

A SQL script, product_listing.sql, is included in extras/product_listing for updating the database.